.TH VAL-SUB 8 "2026-05-30" "versatile-autoreg-val" "System Administration"
.SH NAME
val-sub \- VAL sub-instance daemon
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B val-sub
.I NAME
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B val-sub
runs the full VAL listener loop for a named sub-instance, allowing a
single host to listen to multiple VAS servers or apply different filters
and hooks simultaneously.
.PP
It inherits the base configuration from
.I /etc/val/val.conf
and overrides it with
.IR /etc/val/val.sub/NAME/val.conf .
State and materialised key views are stored independently in
.IR /var/lib/val/sub/NAME/ .
.PP
The UDP bump FIFO is also independent per sub-instance
.RI ( /var/run/val/sub/NAME.bump.fifo )
so each sub-instance can have its own
.B BUMP_LISTEN_PORT
without conflict.
.PP
Log messages are prefixed with
.BI [ NAME-VAL ]
to allow filtering with
.IR journalctl .
.PP
.B val-sub
is normally launched and supervised by
.BR val-sub-manager (8).
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /etc/val/val.sub/NAME/val.conf
Sub-instance configuration.
.TP
.I /etc/val/val.sub/NAME/.enabled
Enables the sub-instance in
.BR val-sub-manager (8).
.TP
.I /var/lib/val/sub/NAME/
State directory: version, clients.json, materialised key views.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR val (8),
.BR val-sub-manager (8),
.BR val-sub-instance (8)
